article_title: National Australia Bank to Sell 28% Stake in U.S. Unit IPO
article_text:
MELBOURNE, Australia—National Australia Bank Ltd. aims to raise at least $336 million by selling a minority stake in its U.S. banking operation via an initial public offering, as the lender focuses on its core businesses in Australia and New Zealand.

In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission on Friday, NAB said it plans to...
